webpackJsonp([0xc1c0c357e0e5],{389:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h1>Forms</h1>\n<p>Inputting any type of information should be clear and to the point. We like to add guidance in context—inside or outside the field—to help people feel supported.</p>\n<h2>General guidelines</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Break large complex forms into smaller simpler patterns</li>\n<li>Form inputs should be tap-friendly</li>\n<li>When possible, forms should support a summary of errors instead of a generic (and unhelpful) error message</li>\n<li>Required form elements should be clearly marked (or implicitly understood)</li>\n<li>Don\'t override user agent styling too much</li>\n<li>When grouping sets of inputs (e.g.: lists of checkbox or radio options), make sure to provide a clear label that set of inputs</li>\n<li>Form elements needs space for hint/error text (like char counters)</li>\n<li>Don\'t remove <code>:focus</code> indication from inputs</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2>Text inputs</h2>\n<p>Text inputs allow users to interact with or input text data. Typically appear in forms or as a searching interface.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=TextInput&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">TextInput</a> (Single-line): For a text input that expects short content, use a single-line text input.</li>\n<li><a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=Textarea&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Textarea</a> (Multi-line): For a text input that expects longform content, use a multi-line text input.</li>\n<li><a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=NumberInput&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">NumberInput</a> (Numeric values): For an input that expects a number.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Best practices</h3>\n<p>Labels should be provided for each input. If a visible label doesn\'t make sense, at least supply a label that is read aloud to screen readers.\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_labelInputs.png" alt="Labeled input example" title="Labeled input example"></p>\n<p>Labels should be stacked on top of inputs. This layout is better for readability and clarity.\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_labelInputsAbove.png" alt="Stacked label example" title="Stacked label example"></p>\n<p>Placeholder text should not be used as a label. Placeholder text is best used to let people know how they might use the input (e.g.: \'Search members\') or to show an example of what kind of text the input expects (e.g.: \'The Seattle Design Systems Meetup\')\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_noPlaceholderAsLabel.png" alt="Don&#x27;t use placeholder as label example" title="Don&#x27;t use placeholder as label example"></p>\n<p>Avoid segmenting inputs for single values (phone numbers, for example, should be a single field)\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_noSplitInputs.png" alt="Don&#x27;t split inputs example" title="Don&#x27;t split inputs example"></p>\n<p>For more information about text inputs, check out the <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=TextInput&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">TextInput</a>, <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=Textarea&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Textarea</a>, and <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=NumberInput&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">NumberInput</a> examples in <a href="https://github.com/meetup/meetup-web-components/">meetup-web-components</a>.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Checkboxes</h2>\n<p>Checkboxes are used to indicate if something is true or false or to indicate selection. Checkboxes allow the selection of multiple options from a set.\nIf <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=Checkbox&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Checkbox</a> doesn\'t suit your needs, also check out <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=TogglePill&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">TogglePills</a> or feel free to design your own toggle referencing the <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=withToggleControl&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">withToggleControl component</a> (e.g.: the \'like\' action on comments uses <code>withToggleControl</code>).</p>\n<h3>Best practices</h3>\n<p>Each checkbox should work independently of any other checkboxes in the form, and toggling a checkbox should only affect <em>that</em> checkbox\'s status unless you\'re designing an interface for a user to make a batch selection (e.g.: select all members).</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Radio buttons</h2>\n<p>Radio buttons allow the selection of a single option from a set. If multiple selection is needed, use a <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=Checkbox&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Checkbox</a>.</p>\n<h3>Best practices</h3>\n<p>For a large number of items, use a <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=SelectInput&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Select input</a> instead\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_useSelectForMany.png" alt="Use dropdown select input for many options" title="Use dropdown select input for many options"></p>\n<p>Don\'t use a <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?knob-checked=true&#x26;knob-className=&#x26;knob-label=This%20is%20a%20radio&#x26;knob-Direction=row&#x26;knob-Selected=one&#x26;selectedKind=RadioButtonGroup&#x26;selectedStory=Basic%20usage&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Radio input</a> for a single field. Radio buttons are for groups\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_noSingleRadio.png" alt="Radios must be in groups" title="Radios must be in groups"></p>\n<p>If a user is allowed to select none of the options, provide an option for the user to select none. This is necessary because once a Radio button is toggled on, it cannot be toggled off without the user making a new selection.\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_provideNullRadioOption.png" alt="Provide a null option in radio groups when appropriate" title="Provide a null option in radio groups when appropriate"></p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Toggle switch</h2>\n<p>Toggle switches are used to indicate whether whether something is enabled or disabled. Toggle switches are like checkboxes, except checkboxes are for making a selection between options, and the the toggle is for turning an option on and off.</p>\n<h3>Best practices</h3>\n<p>For selecting one or more out of a collection, use a set of <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=Checkbox&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Checkboxes</a> or <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?knob-checked=true&#x26;knob-className=&#x26;knob-label=This%20is%20a%20radio&#x26;knob-Direction=row&#x26;knob-Selected=one&#x26;selectedKind=RadioButtonGroup&#x26;selectedStory=Basic%20usage&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Radio inputs</a> instead\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_avoidToggles.png" alt="Use radio or checkbox for collections" title="Use radio or checkbox for collections"></p>\n<p>If a physical switch would work for the action, a toggle is okay to use.</p>\n<p>Use toggle switches with caution, they may be misleading. Native apps often saves the user\'s input from a toggle switch instantly, and most of our flows on the web don\'t save the a user\'s input until a form is submitted.</p>\n<p>Keep in mind that the "switch" metaphor makes more sense for touch-only interfaces.</p>\n<p>For more information about toggle swtiches, check out the <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?selectedKind=ToggleSwitch&#x26;selectedStory=Default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Toggle Switch</a> example in <a href="https://github.com/meetup/meetup-web-components/">meetup-web-components</a>.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Select input</h2>\n<p>Select inputs allow the selection of a single option from a set, and are useful for saving space in the UI.</p>\n<h3>Best practices</h3>\n<p>If a default value doesn\'t make sense, use an empty placeholder option.\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_useEmptyPlaceholder.png" alt="Use a placeholder option for selects that can be null" title="Use a placeholder option for selects that can be null"></p>\n<p>For small sets of options, consider using a set of <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?knob-checked=true&#x26;knob-className=&#x26;knob-label=This%20is%20a%20radio&#x26;knob-Direction=row&#x26;knob-Selected=one&#x26;selectedKind=RadioButtonGroup&#x26;selectedStory=Basic%20usage&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Radio inputs</a> instead. It lets the user see more content at once\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_useRadiosForFew.png" alt="Use set of radio buttons for few options" title="Use set of radio buttons for few options"></p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Date and time picker</h2>\n<p>Date and time pickers are provided as a shortcut for users to select a date or a time instead of having to type one in manually. When designing with a date or time picker, refer to our <a href="/content/timeanddate">time and date content guidelines</a>.</p>\n<h3>Best practices:</h3>\n<p>When using default values, pick a default that make sense in the given context. For example, it wouldn\'t make sense to default the date to "Today" in the event create flow</p>\n<p>Don\'t use a custom date-picking or time-picking interface on mobile web. Instead, let the user retain access to their device\'s native date or time control.\n<img src="/assets/contentImages/dosAndDonts/forms/forms_useNativeDatePicker.png" alt="Use native date pickers" title="Use native date pickers"></p>\n<p>For more information about date and time pickers, check out the <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?knob-checked=true&#x26;knob-className=&#x26;knob-label=This%20is%20a%20radio&#x26;knob-Direction=row&#x26;knob-Selected=one&#x26;selectedKind=CalendarComponent&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">Calendar</a> component, the <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?knob-checked=true&#x26;knob-className=&#x26;knob-label=This%20is%20a%20radio&#x26;knob-Direction=row&#x26;knob-Selected=one&#x26;selectedKind=DateTimeLocalInput&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">DateTimeLocal</a> component, and <a href="https://meetup.github.io/meetup-web-components/?knob-checked=true&#x26;knob-className=&#x26;knob-label=This%20is%20a%20radio&#x26;knob-Direction=row&#x26;knob-Selected=one&#x26;selectedKind=TimeInput&#x26;selectedStory=default&#x26;full=0&#x26;down=1&#x26;left=1&#x26;panelRight=0&#x26;downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-actions%2Factions-panel">TimeInput</a> component</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Forms",supportingContent:null}},allMarkdownRemark:{edges:[{node:{frontmatter:{title:"meetup-web-components",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/components/",topLevelDir:"Components",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Resources",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/resources/",topLevelDir:"Resources",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Overview",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/brand/",topLevelDir:"Brand",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"mup-web",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/components/mup-web/",topLevelDir:"Components",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Basics",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/content/basics/",topLevelDir:"Content",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Color",supportingContent:"colorListing"},fields:{slug:"/design/color/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Layout basics",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/layout/layoutBasics/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Layout"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Creative filters",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/brand/creativefilters/",topLevelDir:"Brand",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Capitalization",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/content/capitalization/",topLevelDir:"Content",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Buttons",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/buttons/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Stripe",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/layout/stripe/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Layout"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Brand voice",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/brand/brandvoice/",topLevelDir:"Brand",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Punctuation",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/content/punctuation/",topLevelDir:"Content",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Icons",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/icons/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Bounds",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/layout/bounds/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Layout"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Brand assets",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/brand/brandassets/",topLevelDir:"Brand",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Spelling and glossary of terms",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/content/spellingandglossary/",topLevelDir:"Content",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Typography",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/typography/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Section",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/layout/section/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Layout"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Time and date",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/content/timeanddate/",topLevelDir:"Content",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Forms",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/forms/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Flex",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/layout/flex/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Layout"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Pronouns",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/content/prounouns/",topLevelDir:"Content",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Social media",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/content/socialmedia/",topLevelDir:"Content",subDir:""}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Chunk",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/layout/chunk/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Layout"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Spacing",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/layout/spacing/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Layout"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"a11y (accessibility)",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/usability/a11y/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Usability"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Sizing",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/layout/sizing/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Layout"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"i18n (internationalization)",supportingContent:null},fields:{slug:"/design/usability/i18n/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Usability"}}},{node:{frontmatter:{title:"Breakpoints",supportingContent:"breakpointListing"},fields:{slug:"/design/layout/breakpoints/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:"Layout"}}}]}},pathContext:{slug:"/design/forms/",topLevelDir:"Design",subDir:""}}}});
